// EXPECT: FAIL:UndefinedBehavior
// SOLVER_ARGS: --main @main --path '^entry'
// SKIP: COMPILER
// [v0.2.2] Regression: reading an uninitialised aggregate cell is UB (SPEC
// rule 3). The solver's `load` used to force its result `is_defined = true`,
// so it would happily concretize a path that loads `%a[0]` (undef) and uses
// the value — a path the strict interpreter rejects, yielding a solver/interp
// divergence. The fix propagates the loaded cell's definedness through the
// load mux; using the undef value then makes the path UNSAT.
//
// The COMPILER skip is required because this UB is value-level definedness:
// a read of an undef cell through a valid, in-bounds, non-null pointer. The
// compiler is a refinement (docs/symirc.md §"Refinement and Undefined Behavior
// Semantics"): undef lowers to a concrete 0 and the load reads it cleanly, so
// the binary exits 0. None of the C target's enabled sanitizers (address,
// undefined, float-cast-overflow, pointer-compare, pointer-subtract) observe
// read-of-undef — that needs MemorySanitizer, which is incompatible with the
// harness's ASan. The solver runner detects this UB via the is_defined path
// constraint. Same rationale as ub_undef_array / ub_undef_struct /
// fail_ub_nested_undef_struct.
fun @main() : i32 {
  let mut %a: [2] i32 = {undef, undef};
  let mut %p: ptr i32 = undef;
  let mut %r: i32 = 0;
^entry:
  %p = addr %a[0];
  %r = load %p;
  ret %r;
}
